The paper proposes a scalable learning method for a hybrid Hidden Markov Model (HMM) with Gaussian Process (GP) emission for sequential time series data clustering. This involves using Stochastic Variational Inference (SVI) and Reparametrized Random Fourier Feature (R-RFF) to reduce training time. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category covers papers on the development of algorithms and models for machine learning. The proposed method for training the hybrid HMM-GP model falls under this category. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category covers papers on the development of intelligent agents and systems. The proposed method for clustering sequential time series data can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.ST (Statistics): This sub-category covers papers on statistical theory and methods. The use of Gaussian Process emission in the hybrid HMM model involves statistical modeling and inference. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): This sub-category covers papers on the analysis and modeling of social and information networks. The proposed method can be applied to analyze time series data from social and information networks.
